text: In the Capital Region, in 2016, there were 111 opioid-related deaths, up 5% from 2015 and in the North Country, in both 2016 & 2015, there were 59 opioid-related deaths.
In 2016, there were 340 opioid-related deaths in the Hudson Valley  -up 15% from 2015- and 343 opioid-related deaths in Western New York -up 11%.
In the Southern Tier in 2016, there were 125 opioid-related deaths, an increase of 39% from 2015
In the Rochester & Finger Lakes region, in 2016, there were 172 opioid-related deaths, a 45% increase from 2015.
In Central New York, in 2016, there were 242 opioid-related deaths, an increase of 53% from just one year before.

For months my colleagues & I have been insistent that any budget agreement include key funding to reverse the spike in opioid deaths. This is a national emergency that’s taken the lives of far too many Americans.
